race.description: Back To The Gift Hotel Handicap (56)
race.comment: SOUTHERN CRESCENT (10) lines up for the first time since September 22. Started the last campaign in good style when in the placings over 1100m at Warrnambool. Has won first-up in the past and most recent trial suggests another big showing is on the cards. ZAMORA (3) broke his maiden four starts back and has not been far away since, most recently when beaten 1.1 lengths into third over 1200m at Dunkeld. Has the pace to settle in the leading division, so the inside alley is a big plus. SHYLEAH (9) has only won one of 16 and the form this prep does not look pretty, but she'll find this much more to her liking and the nice draw is a bonus. KING'S CHAMBER (1) hasn't lived up to the early promise shown when with Danny O'Brien, but has trialled well ahead of the return and could be ready to show something for the new stable. SWEET CITY DANCER (11) was well beaten first up, but is much better suited up to this trip and draws for an improved run.
